The paper discusses intrinsic motivations and open-ended learning in both cognitive robotics and machine learning, which suggests that it could fit into several sub-categories. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper discusses computational models of intrinsic motivations. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses machine learning models that operationalize intrinsic motivations. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses the biological underpinnings of intrinsic motivations. 

cs.RO (Robotics) is also possible as the paper discusses intrinsic motivations in the context of cognitive robotics. 

cs.CYBER (Cybernetics) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the mechanisms and functions of intrinsic motivations in animals and humans, which could be seen as a cybernetic perspective.
